org.sd.cluster.util
Class Partitioner

java.lang.Object
  org.sd.cluster.util.Partitioner
Direct Known Subclasses:
SingleFunctionPartitioner
public abstract class Partitioner
extends java.lang.Object

Abstract utility to partition data based on a key in light of a changing partition function over time.

Extenders must implement the strategy for memorizing and retrieving partitions for keys.

Consumers supply the partitioning strategies as partitionFunction instance that are set over time.

Author:
Spence Koehler

setPartitionFunction

public void setPartitionFunction(Partitioner.PartitionFunction partitionFunction)
(Re)set the current partition function.

Extenders may override to, for example, limit the number of partition functions that may be set or to add logic around changing the function.

Default implementation adds the partitionFunction to the end of the partitionFunctions list.

getPartition

public final int getPartition(java.lang.String key)
Get the partition for the given key.

If the key has been "seen" before, return the partition according to the partition function that originally "saw" it; otherwise, return the partition according to the current partition function.

Parameters:
key - The key for which to get the partition.
Returns:
the partition for the key.
